OL,3,CMan jailed for the 'violent murder' of
OL,4,Chis mum
OL,6,FAdvising her grandson to take his mum
OL,7,Fto the hospital, she was met with the
OL,8,Fresponse that his mum didn't want to
OL,9,Fgo then and would go in the morning.
OL,11,FShe asked for her grandson to put the
OL,12,Fphone near to her daughter and could
OL,13,Fhear that her breathing was erratic.
OL,14,FShe asked him to call an ambulance,
OL,15,Fbut he said he couldn't due to having
OL,16,Fno credit on his phone.
OL,18,FPutting the phone down to call the
OL,19,Fambulance herself, when she tried her
OL,20,Fgrandson on the phone afterwards, she
OL,21,Fdescribed the phone as being 'dead'.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
